('relationship-type', 'uk', 'Home Improvement', 'Describes the relationship between products that are related. If the product is a variation (i.e., a different size or colour) of another product (e.g., "small red helmet" is a variation of "helmet"), enter the value Variation. This must be entered only for the child items. DO NOT PUT IN THIS VALUE FOR VARIATION PARENT ITEMS. \n\nIf the product is an accessory - defined here as another parent SKU that would be appropriate to associate with this parent SKU (e.g., recommending a specific helmet bag to go with a helmet) - of the parent product, enter the value Accessory. DO NOT PUT IN THIS VALUE FOR ACCESSORY CHILD ITEMS.  Accessories can be seen on the www.amazon.com site as "Also Recommended" selections on certain detail product pages.  Please note that you cannot have accessories in this template that are not home improvement items.', 'Select one of the following options:\nAccessory\nVariation', 'Accessory', 'Optional\n\nRequired if parentage is "child".'),
('relationship-type', 'uk', 'Musical Instruments', 'Describes the relationship between products that are related.\n\nIf the product is part of a variation family (i.e., a specific color of an item that is available in several colors), enter the value "Variation".\n\nEnter "Accessory" if the item should be offered on it''s own and as an accessory to another standalone item.', 'Select one of the following values:\nAccessory\nVariation', 'Variation', 'Optional'),
('relationship-type', 'uk', 'Office', 'Describes the relationship between products that are related. \n\nIf the product is a variation (i.e., a different color or size) of another product (e.g., "envelope, size A4" is a variation of "envelope"), enter the value Variation.   DO NOT FILL IN THIS FIELD FOR PARENT PRODUCTS.  \n\nIf the product is an accessory - defined here as another SKU that would be appropriate to associate with this SKU (e.g., recommending a specific type of pen to go with an envelope) - of the parent product, enter the value Accessory.  Accessories can be seen on the www.amazon.co.uk site as "Also Recommended" selections on certain detail product pages.  \n\nPlease note that you cannot have accessories in this template that are not office items.\n\nThis field is required when parent-sku is provided.\n', 'Select one of the following values: \nAccessory\nVariation', 'Accessory', 'Required when column parent-sku is populated.'),
('relationship-type', 'uk', 'Shoes & Accessories', 'Describes the relationship between products that are related. If the product is a variation (i.e., a different size and &gt; or colour) of another product (e.g., "white polo shirt" is a variation of "polo shirt"), enter the value Variation. This is the only value that can be used and must be entered only for the child items. DO NOT PUT IN THIS VALUE FOR PARENT ITEM. If the product is an accessory - defined here as another parent SKU that would be appropriate to associate with this parent SKU (e.g., recommending a specific type of T-Shirt to go with a Pair of Jeans) - of the parent product, enter the value Accessory. DO NOT PUT IN THIS VALUE FOR CHILD ITEMS.  Accessories can be seen on the www.amazon.co.uk site as "Also Recommended" selections on certain detail product pages.  Please note that you cannot have accessories in this template that are not Apparel items.', 'Select one of the following options\nVariation\nAccessory', 'Variation', 'Optional'),
('relationship-type', 'uk', 'Toys', 'Describes the relationship between products that are related.\n\nIf the product is part of a variation family (i.e., a specific color of an item that is available in several colors), enter the value "Variation".\n\nEnter "Accessory" if the item should be offered on it''s own and as an accessory to another standalone item (e.g. a lightbulb as an accessory for a lamp).\n\n', 'Select one of the following options: Variation or Accessory\n', 'Accessory', 'Optional\n\nRequired when column parent-sku is populated.');
